  "explanation": "While embezzlement of $25,000 is a serious breach of trust, the court must weigh all factors before sentencing. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution, indicating remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. The courtroom disruption by a spectator suggesting a 10-year sentence is entirely disregarded, as sentences must be proportionate and based on law, not public emotion. A lengthy prison term is counterproductive for a first-time white-collar offender who is actively repaying the stolen funds. Therefore, a short period of incarceration is appropriate to serve as a deterrent and punishment, to be followed by probation and mandatory completion of the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
